summary: I like the idea that Bucky would speak Russian around Tony not thinking he would understand it. But he does, of course. And one...
body:
I like the idea that Bucky would speak Russian around Tony not thinking he would understand it. But he does, of course. And one day Bucky’s watching Steve ogle over Tony and says to Nat

“I wish they’d just fuck and we could all stop suffering.”

And Steve is so used to them having conversations in Russian that he ignores it at first, but then Tony straight up joins the conversation

“Who?”

Bucky chokes on his water and suddenly Steve’s snapped out of his trance

“What? What did he say?”

Tony and Bucky just have a stare down

Please dear fuck tell me you can’t actually speak Russian is the obvious horror on Bucky’s face

Meanwhile Nat is stifling laughter because she was waiting for Bucky to slip up one day and say some dumb shit around Tony.

And poor Steve is totally lost because nobody will tell him what just happened.

“Who do you wish would ‘just fuck’?” Tony chuckles, switching back to English.

Natasha bursts out laughing this time and Bucky is straight up terrified. Not of answering the question, because he would under different circumstances. But because Steve is right there and will literally kick his ass for this.

Steve pales and his eyes widen, his hands flying to his hair.

“Um,” he stalls, his eyes flickering to Steve for a split second to catch Steve making cut throat signs. It was a quick action on Bucky’s part, but Tony notices. He notices everything.

He turns to look at his teammate, “Steve?”

Steve stills and intertwines his fingers, looking at the ground, “Yes?”

It’s quiet for a few moments before Natasha gets annoyed and groans, heaving herself off the couch.

“Okay, let’s get this out in the open. Tony likes Steve. Steve likes Tony. You’re both too stupid to figure that out on your own. You’re welcome. Come on, Buck. Let’s leave them to it.”

She grabs his arm and hauls him out of the room, but not before he catches a scowl from Steve.

Yeah, he was definitely going to need to order his casket.

summary: Tony’s Daughter Imagine: The Team Meets Tony’s Baby Mama
title: Tony’s Daughter Imagine: The Team Meets Tony’s Baby Mama
body:
“It’s nice to finally you. By your radiant smile and bright eyes, I can tell your daughter’s looks didn’t come from Tony.”

“Thank you, Thor.”

“So you’re not upset that your boyfriend’s gorgeous, successful baby mama is here?”

“Sam, I’m not jealous. That’s his daughter’s mother.”

“ … anyways, Tony starting singing Don’t You Want Me, Baby to me while I was serving drinks. He kept following me and singing until he fell on a table full of leftover food.”

“Really, Tony? You never serenaded me before.”

“I was drunk … and it’s a catchy song. I do a lot of stupid things when I’m drunk.”

“Tony, how about that KISS concert in ‘94? You starting stripping and you threw your—”

“Okay, okay! That was in the past.”
